// Phase 6.2.A.2 — orbital-lift catalog. A "lift" pairs two scenes with a
// direct, fare-gated, clock-advancing transit. Lifts are the diegetic bridge
// between a surface POI and its orbital companion (Von Braun spaceport ↔
// Granada drydock at this slice; Earth-orbit dock complex and Side-colony
// orbital sectors land in later slices).
//
// Unlike the airport `FlightHub` mechanism (which binds 1:1 to an `airport`
// reservedRect in procgen and picks destinations from a list at the ticket
// counter), an orbital lift is a two-endpoint pair with **one** destination
// per side — board the lift kiosk and you go to the other end. No picker
// modal, no multi-route catalog; the only player decision is whether to ride.
//
// Each row fields:
//   id           — stable identifier; referenced by per-scene fixedInteractables
//                  rows that spawn the lift kiosks.
//   labelZh      — full player-facing name (used by debug surfaces only at MVP).
//   shortZh      — the Interactable label on the kiosk.
//   sceneIdA / sceneIdB — the two endpoints. Validated against scenes.json5.
//   durationMin  — in-game minutes the ride costs; clock advances at midpoint.
//   fare         — ¥ deducted up-front (consistent with flights / transit, so a
//                  mid-transition cancel still reflects the commitment).
//   description  — long-form blurb the player-facing UI may surface later.

{
  lifts: [
    {
      id: 'vonBraunGranadaLift',
      labelZh: '冯·布劳恩—格拉纳达轨道升降梯',
      shortZh: '轨道升降梯',
      sceneIdA: 'vonBraunCity',
      sceneIdB: 'granadaDrydock',
      durationMin: 90,
      fare: 500,
      description: '冯·布劳恩航天港后侧的轨道升降梯。乘梯直达格拉纳达船坞群。',
    },
  ],
}
